{{Refimprove|date=October 2017}} {{Infobox football biography |name = Hussein Abdulle |fullname = Hussein Ali Abdulle |birth_date = |birth_place = [[Somalia]] |death_date = 9 May 2017 |death_place = [[Mogadishu]], [[Somalia]] |nationalyears1 = 1960s–1970s |nationalteam1 = [[Somalia national football team|Somalia]] |managerclubs1 = [[Somalia national football team|Somalia]] }}
'''Hussein Ali Abdulle''' (died 9 May 2017 in [[Mogadishu]], [[Somalia]]) was a [[Somalia|Somali]] football coach and former player.
Representing the [[Somalia national football team|''Ocean Stars'']] in many international competitions and matches during the 1960s and 70s, Abdulle was seen as one of Somalia's most respected footballers of his time<ref name="cafonline"/> and went on to coach the national team.
He died on 9 May 2017 aged 71 after a long illness in his Mogadishu home<ref name="cafonline">{{cite web|url=http://www.cafonline.com/en-US/NewsCenter/News/NewsDetails?id=WAJN3enY54mgYdaQHDXQZA==|title=Somali legend Hussein Ali Abdulle passes away|website=Cafonline.com|accessdate=23 October 2017}}</ref> and was interred afterwards.
FIFA President [[Gianni Infantino]] gave his commiserations in a letter to the [[Somali Football Federation]] two days after Abdulle's passing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kubadbile.com/articles/10083/FIFA-president-Gianni-Infantino-sends-Somalia-condolence|title=FIFA president Gianni Infantino sends Somalia condolence|date=12 May 2017|website=Kubadbile.com|accessdate=23 October 2017}}</ref>
