'''Philips van der Aa''' (died after 1586) was a politician in the [[Seventeen Provinces]] and a statesman of the [[Dutch Republic]] during its struggle for independence, the [[Eighty Years' War]]. 

==Biography==
He was born in [[Mechelen]], and was mayor of the city in 1564, but was banished by the [[Duke of Alva]]. He returned on the side of [[William I of Orange|William I, Prince of Orange]] (William the Silent). In 1572, he came back to power in Mechelen by cunning. In 1573 he was assigned as councillor at the court of [[Diederik Sonoy]], and in 1574 he became commander in [[Gorkum]].

